        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "gmnotes": "",
            "short": "",
            "value": "<p>You touch a target with a device you&rsquo;re holding that uses electricity, requiring a melee attack against the target&rsquo;s EAC. Alternatively, you can instead touch an electrical device a target is wearing (or a target that is an electrical device, such as a robot) with your hand, gaining a +2 bonus to your attack roll. Either way, if your attack hits, the electrical device surges out of control, dealing 4d6 electricity damage to your target.</p>\n<p>Casting this spell doesn&rsquo;t provoke attacks of opportunity.</p>",
